==English==

===Etymology===
from the idea that there is a horse (for example) who is made to move by the [[lure]] of a carrot placed just out of reach, and the threat of being hit by the stick, resulting in the horse moving forward

===Adjective===
'''stick-and-carrot'''

# shortened form of the etymological concept, using both encouragement or promises of good things and also the threat of bad things
#:Example:  It's a stick-and-carrot approach.